><strong>The Clownfish Chrome Extension:</strong> Also from Bogdan Sharkov, this browser extension allows you to use Clownfish voice effects within Google Chrome for web-based applications. It can be found on the Chrome Web Store. The developer's site, <a href=\"https://clownfish-translator.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">clownfish-translator.com</a>, is also associated with this.</li>\n  <li><strong>Unofficial Mobile Apps:</strong> You might encounter mobile applications on platforms like the Google Play Store that use names similar to \"Clownfish Voice Changer\" (e.g., \"ClownFish Voice Changer Effect\"). It's crucial to know that these are typically developed by <em>different, unaffiliated entities</em> and are functionally distinct from the official desktop and Chrome versions. This guide does not cover these unofficial mobile apps.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This clarification ensures you are looking for and using the correct, official software to get the best and safest experience.</p>\n\n<h2>Key Features of Clownfish Voice Changer (Windows Desktop App)</h2>\n<p><strong>Clownfish Voice Changer</strong> is celebrated for packing a surprising punch for a completely <strong>free voice changer</strong>. Its standout characteristic is its system-level integration on Windows – once configured, it modifies your microphone input across all applications, from Discord and Skype to your favorite online games.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th><strong>Feature Category</strong></th>\n<th><strong>Description</strong></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Core Voice Modulation</strong></td>\n<td>A diverse list of pre-set <strong>voice effects</strong> including Alien, Atari, Clone, Mutation (Fast/Slow variations), Male pitch, Female pitch, Helium pitch, Baby pitch, Radio, Robot. Also features a \"Custom pitch\" slider for fine-tuning and a \"Clear effect\" button to instantly revert to your natural voice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Real-Time Processing</strong></td>\n<td>Applies all voice alterations instantaneously, making it perfectly suited for live interactions in gaming, streaming, and voice calls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Audio Utilities Suite</strong></td>\n<td>\n  <strong>Music Player:</strong> Integrated player, similar to VLC, for playing local audio files or background music during your sessions.<br/>\n  <strong>Soundboard:</strong> A robust system for playing pre-recorded sounds or custom audio clips, often triggerable with keyboard hotkeys, enhancing streams and gaming.<br/>\n  <strong>Text-to-Speech (TTS):</strong> Converts typed text into spoken words using various voice options, supporting an impressive range of languages.\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Advanced Customization & Control</strong></td>\n<td>\n  <strong>Effect Mixture:</strong> Allows the combination of two or more existing voice effects to generate new, unique vocal sounds.<br/>\n  <strong>Vocoder:</strong> Synthesizes your voice by combining it with a chosen waveform for creative sound design.<br/>\n  <strong>Microphone Sensitivity/Noise Gate:</strong> Lets you adjust the microphone input level and acts as a noise gate to cut off audio when your voice drops below a certain quietness threshold (<strong>use with care</strong> not to set too high).<br/>\n  <strong>Append Original Voice:</strong> An option to layer your unaltered voice with the modified one, which can sometimes improve the clarity and intelligibility of speech.\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>VST Plugin Support</strong></td>\n<td>One of its most significant advanced features. Clownfish allows the integration of third-party <strong>Virtual Studio Technology (VST) plugins</strong>, which vastly expands the potential for sound customization and professional-grade audio effects, similar to Digital Audio Workstations (DAWs).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Operating System Compatibility</strong></td>\n<td>The primary desktop application is heavily focused on the <strong>Windows</strong> operating system. It is compatible with both 32-bit and 64-bit versions, generally from Windows 7 up to Windows 11. The full desktop experience is not officially offered for macOS or Linux.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>This \"all-in-one\" approach provides considerable value, making Clownfish a versatile toolkit for many users, despite some specialized software offering more polish in individual features.</p>\n\n<h2>Installation Guide for Clownfish Voice Changer (Windows Desktop)</h2>\n<p>Getting started with your <strong>Clownfish Voice Changer download</strong> and installation is a key first step. Follow this guide carefully to integrate this powerful free tool into your Windows system.</p>\n\n<p><strong>1. Navigate to the Official Website</strong>: For a safe download, free from bundled unwanted software, always start by visiting the official Clownfish Voice Changer desktop application website: <strong><a href=\"https://clownfishvoicechanger.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://clownfishvoicechanger.net/</a></strong>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>2. Download the Correct Version</strong>: On the website, find the 'Download' section. You will see options for different versions of Clownfish, typically for 64-bit and 32-bit Windows systems. Most modern PCs use 64-bit Windows; if you're unsure, check your system properties. Download the version that matches your system's architecture to ensure compatibility.</p>\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-53 \" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/1.webp\" alt=\"Official Clownfish Voice Changer website download page for Windows showing 64-bit and 32-bit options\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<p><strong>3. Initiate the Installation Process</strong>: Once you've downloaded the correct '.exe' installer file, double-click it to begin. The setup wizard will then guide you through the installation steps.</p>\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-54 \" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/2-e1711646743644-300x29.webp\" alt=\"Starting the Clownfish Voice Changer setup wizard executable\" width=\"362\" height=\"35\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55 \" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/3.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer installation wizard - License agreement step\" width=\"601\" height=\"457\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<p><strong>4. Opt for a Complete Installation (Recommended)</strong>: During the setup, you might be asked about which components to install. For access to all features and voice effects, it's usually best to select the complete or default installation option.</p>\n\n<img class=\" wp-image-56 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/4.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer installation wizard - Selecting components to install\" width=\"600\" height=\"459\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<p><strong>5. Specify Installation Location</strong>: The wizard will prompt you to choose an installation directory. Clownfish is a lightweight application (typically requiring only a few megabytes), so it can be installed on any preferred drive or partition.</p>\n\n<img class=\" wp-image-57 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/5.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer installation wizard - Choosing the install location\" width=\"600\" height=\"429\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<p><strong>6. Close Interfering Programs (If Prompted)</strong>: The installer may advise you to close other running applications that could interfere with the setup process. Follow such prompts to ensure a smooth and error-free installation.</p>\n\n<img class=\" wp-image-58 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/6.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer installation wizard - Prompt to close interfering programs\" width=\"601\" height=\"460\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<p><strong>7. Restart Your Audio Service (If Prompted)</strong>: It's common for a command prompt window to appear during installation, asking for permission to restart your computer's audio service. This is a critical step for Clownfish to integrate with your system's audio. If it doesn't proceed automatically, type “Y” and press “Enter” when prompted.</p>\n\n<img class=\" wp-image-59 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/7.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer installation - Command prompt window for audio service restart\" width=\"600\" height=\"127\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<img class=\" wp-image-60 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/8.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer installation - Confirming audio service restart in CMD\" width=\"600\" height=\"127\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<p><strong>8. Completing the Installation</strong>: Follow any remaining prompts in the setup wizard. After the installation is complete, click 'Finish'. It's <strong>highly recommended to restart your computer</strong> at this point to ensure all components are correctly initialized and integrated with your system.</p>\n\n<img class=\" wp-image-61 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/9.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer installation wizard successfully completed - Finish screen\" width=\"603\" height=\"365\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<p>Congratulations! <strong>You have successfully installed Clownfish Voice Changer.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Important Note on Using Clownfish:</strong> Unlike many applications, Clownfish Voice Changer doesn't usually open a main program window when you click its desktop icon. Instead, it <strong>runs discreetly in the background</strong>. You manage and control it via its icon located in the Windows system tray (the area near your clock, usually at the bottom-right of your screen). <strong>Right-click this icon to access all its features and settings.</strong> This behavior can be confusing for first-time users, so remember to look for it there!</p>\n\n<img class=\" wp-image-62 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/10.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer icon located and active in Windows system tray after successful installation\" width=\"600\" height=\"470\" / loading=\"lazy\" />\n\n<h3>How to Configure Clownfish Correctly: Your Essential Setup Guide</h3>\n<p>Properly configuring <strong>Clownfish Voice Changer</strong>, especially your microphone, is the <strong>most critical step</strong> to ensure it works smoothly and avoids common user frustrations. This <strong>Clownfish setup</strong> guide will walk you through it carefully.</p>\n<ol>\n <li><strong>Locating Clownfish in System Tray</strong>: After installation and a PC restart, find the Clownfish icon in your Windows system tray. You might need to click the small upward-pointing arrow (often labeled \"Show hidden icons\") to see all active tray icons.</li>\n <p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-67 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/11.webp\" alt=\"Finding the Clownfish Voice Changer icon among other icons in the Windows system tray\" width=\"330\" height=\"249\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n <li><strong>Opening the Setup Menu</strong>: Right-click on the Clownfish tray icon. This will open its main context menu. From this menu, select \"Setup,\" and then click on \"System Integration.\" This is where you'll tell Clownfish which microphone to use.</li>\n <p><img class=\" wp-image-68 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/12.webp\" alt=\"Right-clicking Clownfish system tray icon and selecting the 'Setup  loading=\"lazy\" /> System Integration' menu option\" width=\"600\" height=\"611\" /></p>\n <li><strong>Choosing and Installing the Correct Microphone</strong>: The \"System Integration\" window will display a list of all microphones detected by your Windows system.\n    <ul>\n        <li>Clownfish needs to \"install\" its driver onto your desired microphone to modify its output. The microphone it's currently configured to use might have a status like \" (installed - click to remove)\" or simply show \"-installed\" next to its name in the list.</li>\n        <li><strong>Crucial Step:</strong> If your preferred microphone is not the one selected (or if no microphone appears correctly set up for Clownfish), you may need to first click \"Remove\" next to any incorrectly assigned microphone. Then, find your primary microphone in the list and click the \"Install\" button next to it. <strong>Only one microphone should be \"installed\" for Clownfish at a time to avoid conflicts.</strong></li>\n        <li><strong>Verify Windows Settings:</strong> After this, it's vital to ensure that this same microphone (the one you just \"installed\" Clownfish onto) is also set as your <strong>Default Recording Device</strong> in your main Windows Sound settings (usually found via Control Panel > Sound > Recording tab). Any mismatch between Clownfish's target microphone and Windows' default microphone is a very common reason why <strong>Clownfish Voice Changer not working</strong> issues occur.</li>\n    </ul>\n </li>\n <p><img class=\" wp-image-70 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/14.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer 'System Integration' window showing list of microphones for setup and installation\" width=\"600\" height=\"345\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n <li><strong>Activating Clownfish & Selecting Voice Effects</strong>:\n    <ul>\n        <li>First, ensure Clownfish is actually turned on. Right-click the tray icon; if the option says \"Turn On,\" click it to activate the software. If it says \"Turn Off,\" then Clownfish is already active and processing audio.</li>\n        <li>To choose a voice effect, right-click the tray icon again, and this time select \"Set voice changer.\" A menu will pop up, populated with the various <strong>voice effects</strong> Clownfish offers (e.g., Alien, Atari, Robot, Male pitch, Female pitch). Simply click on an icon to activate that voice effect instantly.</li>\n        <li>To revert to your original, unmodified voice, select the \"Clear effect\" option from this same menu (it's usually located at the top or bottom of the effects list).</li>\n        <li><strong>Testing Your Voice:</strong> To hear your modified voice for testing purposes, right-click the Clownfish tray icon and check the \"Hear Microphone\" option. Your changed voice will play through your speakers/headphones. <strong>Remember to uncheck this option during normal use if you experience an echo</strong>, especially if you're using speakers or have the \"Hear music/sound\" option enabled for the soundboard.</li>\n    </ul>\n</li>\n <p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-71 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/15.webp\" alt=\"Selecting a specific voice effect like 'Alien' or 'Robot' from the Clownfish Voice Changer effects menu\" width=\"267\" height=\"509\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n <li><strong>Integration with Other Programs (Discord, Skype, Games, etc.)</strong>: Once Clownfish Voice Changer is active and correctly configured to modify your default system microphone, other applications (like Discord, Skype, Zoom, OBS, or your online games) should automatically use the voice with the applied effect. However, for best results and to troubleshoot:\n    <ul>\n        <li>Open the audio/voice settings within the specific application you want to use Clownfish with (e.g., in Discord, go to User Settings > Voice & Video).</li>\n        <li>In that application's settings, ensure that the \"Input Device\" is set to your \"Default\" system microphone. Since Clownfish modifies the default system microphone at a driver level, this selection should carry over the voice change. In some cases, Clownfish might also create a virtual microphone device (e.g., \"Microphone (Clownfish Audio)\") in your system's audio devices list; if so, you might try selecting that directly within the application.</li>\n    </ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-72 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/16.webp\" alt=\"Configuring the input device in Discord audio settings to ensure Clownfish Voice Changer modified audio is used\" width=\"604\" height=\"755\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<p>By carefully following these <strong>Clownfish setup</strong> steps, particularly the microphone configuration, you should have Clownfish Voice Changer working effectively to enhance your online communication and content creation. Remember, a little patience during setup can save a lot of frustration later!</p>\n\n<h3>Downloading and Installing Plugins for Clownfish Voice Changer</h3>\n<p>Enhancing <strong>Clownfish Voice Changer</strong> with plugins can add significant customization and functionality. This section will guide you through installing plugins, using \"Push2Talk\" (which allows toggling voice effects with a hotkey) as an example.</p>\n<h4>Downloading Plugins</h4>\n<p><strong>1. Access the Downloads Section</strong>: Go to the official <strong><a href=\"https://clownfishvoicechanger.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Clownfish Voice Changer website</a></strong>. In the 'Download' area, you'll usually find a dedicated section for plugins alongside the main application versions.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Select and Download Your Desired Plugin</strong>: For this example, we'll use the Push2Talk plugin. Click to download its .zip file. This plugin introduces a push-to-talk feature, enabling voice effects only while a specific key is pressed.</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-73 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/17.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer website's download page showing available plugins like Push2Talk\" width=\"600\" height=\"265\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-74 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/18.webp\" alt=\"Close-up of the Push2Talk plugin download link on the Clownfish website\" width=\"334\" height=\"64\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<h4>Extracting the Plugin</h4>\n<p><strong>1. Unzip the Downloaded File</strong>: After the download is complete, locate the .zip file and extract its contents into a new folder on your computer. This step is essential for accessing the plugin files needed for installation.</p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-75 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/19.webp\" alt=\"Windows Explorer showing extracted files from the Push2Talk plugin zip archive\" width=\"466\" height=\"78\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<h4>Installing the Plugin</h4>\n<p><strong>1. Locate the Clownfish Installation Directory</strong>: Navigate to where you installed Clownfish Voice Changer. The default path is often `C:\\Program Files (x86)\\ClownfishVoiceChanger\\` or `C:\\Program Files\\ClownfishVoiceChanger\\`. If you chose a custom path during installation, go there instead.</p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-76 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/20.webp\" alt=\"Navigating to the Clownfish Voice Changer installation folder in Program Files (x86)\" width=\"179\" height=\"26\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-77 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/21.webp\" alt=\"Viewing the contents of the Clownfish Voice Changer program files directory\" width=\"421\" height=\"29\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>2. Transfer the Plugin Files</strong>: Open the folder where you extracted the plugin files. Select the relevant files (often a `.dll` file, like `PushToTalk.dll`, and sometimes other associated files) and drag or copy them into the `Plugins` sub-folder within your Clownfish installation directory. If a `Plugins` folder doesn't exist, you might need to create one, or the specific plugin might need to be placed directly in the main Clownfish directory (<strong>always check if the plugin comes with a README or instructions</strong>).</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-78 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/22.webp\" alt=\"Copying PushToTalk plugin .dll files into the Clownfish Voice Changer plugins subfolder\" width=\"601\" height=\"148\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-79 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/23.webp\" alt=\"PushToTalk plugin files successfully copied and placed in the Clownfish installation folder\" width=\"600\" height=\"216\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>3. Create a Desktop Shortcut (for executable plugins)</strong>: Some plugins might be standalone executables that work alongside Clownfish (e.g., a separate hotkey manager). If your plugin has an `.exe` file, you can right-click it in the Clownfish directory and select 'Send to > Desktop (create shortcut)' for easier access.</p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-80 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/24.webp\" alt=\"Creating a desktop shortcut for a Clownfish Voice Changer plugin's executable file\" width=\"599\" height=\"178\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<h4>Activating and Using the Plugin</h4>\n<p><strong>1. Restart Clownfish</strong>: To ensure Clownfish recognizes and loads the new plugin, it's usually necessary to restart the application. Right-click on the Clownfish system tray icon, select 'Turn off,' wait a few seconds, then right-click again and select 'Turn on'.</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-81 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/25.webp\" alt=\"Restarting Clownfish Voice Changer application using the system tray icon menu options\" width=\"602\" height=\"540\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>2. Using the Plugin (Push2Talk Example)</strong>: If the plugin has a separate executable or configuration (like the desktop shortcut for Push2Talk), open it. For Push2Talk, you should see an option to 'Set hotkey'. Click this, press your desired key, and then click 'Apply'. Once configured, pressing and holding this hotkey should activate your selected Clownfish voice effect, and releasing it should deactivate the effect. Other plugins might add new options directly into Clownfish's right-click menu.</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-83 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/27.webp\" alt=\"Configuring the specific hotkey for the Push2Talk plugin for Clownfish Voice Changer\" width=\"605\" height=\"294\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<h4>For Other Plugins</h4>\n<p><strong>1. The general process for installing other Clownfish plugins is similar to the steps outlined above</strong>. However, always check if a specific plugin comes with its own installation instructions or README file. By downloading, installing, and configuring plugins, you can significantly customize your voice-changing experience to fit your needs.</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-84 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/28.webp\" alt=\"A list of various other plugins available for download for Clownfish Voice Changer\" width=\"609\" height=\"87\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<h3>Clownfish Terminal Edition: Voice Changing via Command Line</h3>\n<p>For users who prefer command-line interfaces, or for use on systems like Linux and macOS where the main GUI app isn't supported, <strong>Clownfish Voice Changer</strong> offers a <strong>Terminal Edition</strong>. This streamlined version provides core voice modulation from a terminal window.</p>\n<h4>Accessing Terminal Edition</h4>\n<p><strong>1. Navigate to the Downloads Section</strong>: On the official <strong><a href=\"https://clownfishvoicechanger.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Clownfish website</a></strong>, go to the 'Downloads' page. Scroll down to find the \"Terminal Sound Player & Effect List\" or similarly named sections for Windows, Linux, and macOS Terminal Editions.</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-85 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/29.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer official website downloads page highlighting Terminal Edition options for various OS\" width=\"600\" height=\"426\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<h4>Downloading and Extracting</h4>\n<p><strong>1. Choose Your Operating System</strong>: Select and download the Terminal Edition .zip file appropriate for your OS (Windows, Linux, or macOS).</p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-86 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/30.webp\" alt=\"Specific download links for Clownfish Voice Changer Terminal Edition for Windows, Linux, and macOS\" width=\"299\" height=\"59\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n<p><strong>2. Download and Unzip</strong>: After the download, extract the contents of the .zip file to a folder on your computer.</p>\n\n<h4>Launching Terminal Edition</h4>\n<p><strong>1. Execute the Program</strong>: Open your terminal or command prompt, navigate to the extracted folder, and run the Clownfish Terminal Edition executable file (the exact command will vary by OS).</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-87 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/31.webp\" alt=\"Clownfish Voice Changer Terminal Edition executable file shown within its extracted folder\" width=\"501\" height=\"96\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n<p><strong>2. Exploring the Interface</strong>: A terminal window will open, providing access to Clownfish's features via text commands. This allows for efficient control over voice effects and settings without a graphical interface.</p>\n<p><img class=\" wp-image-88 aligncenter\" src=\"/uploads/2024/03/32.webp\" alt=\"Screenshot of the Clownfish Voice Changer Terminal Edition running in a command line window interface\" width=\"603\" height=\"296\" / loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n\n<h4>Benefits of the Terminal Edition</h4>\n<p>The <strong>Clownfish Terminal Edition is excellent for users comfortable with command-line tools</strong>, those on Linux/macOS, or in environments where GUI applications are not ideal (like servers or remote setups). It provides Clownfish's powerful voice modulation with minimal resource consumption.</p>\n\n<h3>Clownfish Voice Changer as a Chrome Extension</h3>\n<p>For quick, browser-based voice changing without a full software installation, the <strong>Clownfish Voice Changer Chrome Extension</strong> offers a convenient solution. Developed by Bogdan Sharkov (the same developer as the desktop app), it integrates directly into Google Chrome.</p>\n<h4>Adding the Clownfish Extension</h4>\n<p><strong>1. Navigate to the Chrome Web Store</strong>: You can find the extension by searching \"Clownfish Voice Changer\" in the Chrome Web